    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the simulation evidence on the basis that (1) Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification bounds the NIH prediction interval below the clinical threshold with 90% confidence, and (2) the interim model revision of 2025-12-05 was judged non-material to the hemolysis scalar dataset collected on 2025-11-14. No formal re-validation against the revised model build was performed to substantiate this materiality judgment, constituting the W-EP-03 stale-input weakness. The decision is recorded as Accepted pending regulatory reviewer scrutiny of the dataset vintage gap.",
